
# Expense Tracker CLI

Expense Tracker CLI is a command line application for managing personal transactions. It allows users to add, update, delete and view transactions as well as filter by type, category, user and more
## Features

- Add transaction(Income or expense)
- Update existing transaction

- Delete Transactions 

- Search for transaction by type, user or ID 

- Generate transaction summary by user(total income, expenses and net balance) 

- View user information and transactions by ID or name


## Installation

Install my-project with npm

### Clone the project to your computer

```bash
  git clone git@github.com:rovenelabanga001/Expense_tracker_CLI.git
```
### Navigate to the project directory
```bash
cd Expense_tracker_CLI.git
```
### Install dependencies
```bash
pipenv install
```
### Setup virtual environment
```bash
pipenv shell
```
### Run the app
```bash
python cli.py
```

    
## Usage
### Running the application
```bash
python cli.py
```

### The app will display a menu with available options. You can choose from

- Create User 
- Update User 
- Delete User 
- Create Transaction 
- Update Transaction 
- Delete Transaction 
- Assign Transaction to User 
- Search for user by name 
- Search for user by ID 
- List Users 
- List Transactions 
- View Transactions by User 
- Search for transactions by type 
- Search for transaction by ID 
- View user's transaction summary - Exit

## Project Structure

```
Expense_tracker_CLI/
├── alembic.ini
├── cli.py
├── models.py
├── README.md
└── migrations/
    ├── env.py
    └── versions/
```


- **cli.py** Contains the main CLI application logic. It handles user input, interacts with the database, and manages the flow of the program. 
- **models.py** Defines the database models (Transaction and User). It also includes relationships and data validation for transactions and users.
## Dependecies
This project relies on the following Python packages: 
- **[SQLAlchemy](https://www.sqlalchemy.org/):** A powerful and flexible SQL toolkit and Object-Relational Mapping (ORM) library for Python. 
- **[Alembic](https://alembic.sqlalchemy.org/):** A database migration tool for managing version control of your SQLAlchemy models.
